div.p:
An example ZooBank page (
   
    Gasterosteus Saltatrix Linnaeus, 1766
   ), illustrating several GNUB services: (1) user authentication; (2) “fuzzy” searching of GNUB content; (3) APIs and services; (4) ZooBank registration; (5) External Identifier cross-linking; (6) BHL page linking; (7) similar/related name discovery (via GNI’s name searching service); and (8) multi-lingual support. Not shown are services to manage user accounts, de-duplicate records, prototype reconciliation tools, services for journal publishers, and visualization tools for author publication history and other statistics.
